Four suspects linked to a cartel believed to have swindled unsuspecting teachers millions of shillings will remain in police custody for 14 days to allow police complete investigations. The suspects are being accused of swindling the teachers by promising them employment, promotions and transfers. Snd as&nbsp;Shadrack Mitty reports, some of the alleged masterminds are former and current employees of the teachers&rsquo; service commission.
